net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component

Interface ParentComponent

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Component, java.lang.Iterable<Component>, LocaleContextSource
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractLazyInit, AbstractSimpleValueEditor, CalendarDateRange, CalendarValueEditor, CardContainer, CheckboxValueEditor, ClickToEditComponent, ClickToEditForm, CollapsibleContainer, ComboBoxValueEditor, Container, DataColumnTable, DateComponent, Dialog, EmptyTableHider, Frame, HistoryContainer, LocaleSelector, LocalizedTextEditor, Media, Menu, MessageContainer, NumberEditor, OptionDialog, Pager, PopupMenu, ProgrammaticIdentifierEditor, PropertyEditor, SearchUIImpl, TabbedContainerImpl, Table, TextEditor, Window, WindowContainer

    public interface ParentComponent
extends Component
    The parent component interface must be implemented by any Component implementation that has child objects. This is necessary as several methods need special attention for parent components.
    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • contains

        boolean contains(Component com)
        Check if this component contains the given component. The check is made based on object identity. This method will not traverse deeper than this parent object. For example, if this parent component contains another parent component which contains the argument, the return value will be false.
        Parameters:
        com - The component.
        Returns:
        true if the argument is contained in this parent component.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the argument is null.

      • remove

        void remove(Component com)
        Remove the child component from this component. This does not close the component. It can be re-added to this or another component.
        Parameters:
        com - The child component.
